CP6364 
Description of Operation 
Duplex Alternating Pump 
Control Panel 
 
 Repeat Cycle Timer Program DRCT v2.0 
 
 
1. Upon power up at panel there is a 2-minute time delay before a pump can start. 
2. Pump 1 will start when tank level 2 is reached and stop when the tank is pumped 
down to level 1. 
3. On the next cycle pump 2 will operate similarly.  Pumps alternate each time the tank 
level falls below level 1. 
4. If a clock timer or repeat cycle timer program is utilized, then pumping is allowed 
only at certain times even if level 2 is reached. 
5. If the timer is keeping the pumps from running and high level is reached, then an 
alarm will occur, and pump 2 will start for 10 minutes.  After pump 2 shuts off and if 
level 1 has not been reached, then pump 1 will run for 10 minutes. 
6. If after an item 5 event occurs once, and level 1 has not been reached, then the pumps 
will go back to their original pumping schedule and the next time a high level occurs, 
the pumps will not override the timer.  This will be an indication of a pumping 
problem. 
7. If during an item 5 event level 1 is reached, then the system will reset and an item 5 
event can reoccur. 
8. Pumps will not operate simultaneously in automatic mode.

Setting the PLC 
CP6364 
 
Upon power up, if time and date are not showing, use down arrow to scroll until the time and date 
appear. 
 
To enter into program mode hit ESC once. Arrow down to desired selection and hit OK.  
 
 
To set clock, arrow down to SETUP, scroll to CLOCK, and hit OK once, scroll 
down to SET CLOCK press OK. Use LEFT and RIGHT arrow keys to 
maneuver around and the UP and DOWN keys to change setting. Once complete hit 
OK. To get back to main screen hit ESC. 
 
 
To set parameters, arrow down to PROGRAM then arrow to SET PARAMETERS 
and hit OK twice.  Use LEFT and RIGHT arrow keys to maneuver around and 
the UP and DOWN keys to change the parameters. Once clock is set hit OK.  Once 
complete hit ESC 3 times to return to the main screen.  
 
Parameters: 
 
B28  Pump Run Time and Off Time 
 
 
Note: 
 
1) To view inputs, at the main screen (clock showing) hit the RIGHT arrow key. To 
return to main screen hit LEFT arrow key. 
 
2) To view outputs, at the main screen (clock showing) hit the RIGHT arrow key twice. 
To return to main screen hit LEFT arrow key twice. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
    Parameter B28 
     Pump run time. 
     Pump off time. 
 
     Current time in PLC 
      (Not settable, could be another number, may be changing 
        continuously.) Disregard.
